There seems to be a sort of unintended pathos in the few words of the record that tell us this. The Founder gives them Grif and Tilston to start them on their laborious course ; and then, some years afterwards, no one interfering on their behalf in the slow toilsome interval, a. neighbour steps in and bestows upon them a. not very important donation at Hesketh, the total value of which, with the additions afterwards made to it, only mounted, at the time of the Dissolution, to 34, 13s. 4d. a year. And then they have to wait until 1145 for Walter Espee's supplementary grant of Bildes- dale, which, eventually at least, constituted a. valuable addition to their worldly means.
